ABCDv5.1 Longitudinal depRS

2025-02-19

Elastic net linear regression using glmnet

Model predicting year 2 CBCL using environmental factors measured at baseline.

Data prep

N = 8975 individuals with CBCL data at year 2

N = 7033 individuals with complete CBCL and predictor data.
N = 4 individuals identifying as gender non-conforming were excluded.

N = 7029 split into training 80/% (N = 5622) and test 20/% (N = 1407) samples.

CBCL DSM5-oriented depression subscale

23 predictors were included.

Although glmnet standardises data by default, coefficients are returned on their original scales. To get standardised coefficients for applying to other data, Im scaling the raw data before inputting to glmnet. Each elastic net model is run with 10-fold cross-validation and lambda/alpha values are selected based on minimising the model mean squared error (MSE).
